	   <tr><td colspan=2>As an 11th level barb shaman new to the class, I am not sure if what I do is right, but here goes:<br><br>Light Healing<br>Sicken<br>Tainted Breath<br>Inner Fire<br>Scale Skin<br>Strengthen<br>Serpent Sight<br>Spirit of Wolf<br><br>I keep lots of buffs handy because we really only have two good damage spells at this level, and I always keep a heal handy. I swap out gate or cure disease/poison when need calls, but mainly I keep the buffs for ambush buffing and assisting my groups, where I am usually just a buffer/backup healer. My 2cp<br><br>Tashtego of Saryrn<br>11th level Shaman of the Tribunal<br>"These Southerners surely like rain, don't they?"<br>&nbsp;<br>-- <br>Lord Lambeau Farstrider<br>Human Druid of Tunare<br>Lords and Ladies<br>Saryrn<br>"Port: Don't leave home without it."<br><br></td></tr>
